Name: PHOTO COVERAGE SCALE
Explanation: THE DENOMINATOR OF THE RATIO BETWEEN THE DISTANCE ON A PHOTOGRAPH (NUMERATOR) AND THE CORRESPONDING DISTANCE ON THE EARTH'S SURFACE (DENOMINATOR), WITH THE NUMERATOR FIXED AS 1.

Name: IMAGERY SCALE
Explanation: THE PHOTOGRAPHIC PRINT SCALE SPECIFIED BY AN ALPHABETIC CODE.

Name: SCALE OF PRINTS
Explanation: THE DENOMINATOR OF THE RATIO BETWEEN THE DISTANCE ON A PHOTOGRAPH (NUMERATOR) AND THE CORRESPONDING DISTANCE ON A PRINT (DENOMINATOR), WITH THE NUMERATOR FIXED AS 1.

Name: IMAGERY SCALE NUMERIC
Explanation: THE PHOTOGRAPHIC PRINT SCALE SPECIFIED AS A NUMERICAL VALUE UP TO 99000 (E.G. 25000 = A SCALE OF 1 TO 25000).
